in Detail
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
PHASE - 3: File Server Setup

----------------------------------------

Configured FS01 as a File Server on a Host-Only Network.

IP Address: 192.168.10.20

Configuration Steps:

Installed Windows Server.

Joined the domain.

Added File Server role.

Created department folders:

------------------------------------

HR

Accounts

Sales

Procurement

Logistics

Warehouse

Public

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

- Set NTFS permissions to control access at the file system level.

- Configured Share permissions for network access.

- Created Active Directory groups (e.g., HR Users, Accounts Users) for   permission management.

- Mapped network drives using Group Policy with item-level targeting for 

precise access control.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Folder Sharing Structure Example

-----------------------------------------------------------

- HR Department folder: Accessible and listable by all HR group users.

Inside HR folder: Individual user folders (e.g., Arun Kumar) where users   cannot delete the folder but can delete items inside.

- Common file sharing folder: Accessible only to HR group users for sharing files.

- IT Admins have full control to delete files, while users cannot delete files in the common folder.

- All department groups have access and write permissions as appropriate.

*** 

This setup ensures secure, organized, and efficient file sharing across departments, with tailored permissions to meet organizational needs.
